{"id":29569,"title":"Where there's smoke there must be ire! Nicotine addiction treatment: a review.","abstract":"Tobacco use in the United States has decreased by almost 50 percent since 1965, although the decline over the past few years has stalled. In the high school student population the smoking rates have not only plateaued over the past several years but have even increased. This paper will discuss the pathophysiology of tobacco addiction and treatment options for smoking cessation.","date":"2014-03-20","categories":"Chemically-Induced Disorders","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24645304","annotations":[{"name":"Smoking","weight":0.794971,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Smoking"},{"name":"United States","weight":0.742176,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States"},{"name":"Smoking cessation","weight":0.676801,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Smoking_cessation"},{"name":"Tobacco smoking","weight":0.660386,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tobacco_smoking"},{"name":"Tobacco","weight":0.631541,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tobacco"},{"name":"Nicotine","weight":0.597067,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nicotine"},{"name":"Substance dependence","weight":0.493596,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Substance_dependence"},{"name":"High school","weight":0.381513,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/High_school"},{"name":"Drug rehabilitation","weight":0.249266,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drug_rehabilitation"},{"name":"Pathophysiology","weight":0.221708,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pathophysiology"},{"name":"Nicotine addiction","weight":0.218202,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nicotine_addiction"},{"name":"School","weight":0.0805305,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/School"},{"name":"Population","weight":0.0543856,"wikipedia_article":"